articles.author: Dan Sullivan
articles.title: Floridians advised to plan as chance of storm in Gulf increases - Tampa Bay Times
articles.description: The system near Central America remains disorganized, but is likely to develop into a storm late this week in the Gulf of Mexico.
articles.content:
Weather forecasters continue to eye a broad area of low pressure near Central America that could develop into a tropical storm or a hurricane and affect Florida late this week.
